H. No. 7820 / 62 OG No. 19, 3136 (May 9, 1966)

[ REPUBLIC ACT NO. 4190, May 04, 1965 ]

AN ACT DECLARING CERTAIN PLACES IN THE PROVINCE OF LANAO DEL SUR AS NATIONAL PARKS.

Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives of the Philippines in Congress assembled:

SECTION 1. The following places in the Province of Lanao del Sur are hereby declared as national parks:

Rungkiman Park, located in the Municipality of Ramain;

Lake Dapao, located in the Municipality of Pualas;

Lake Butig, located in the Municipality of Butig;

Sacred Mountain together with all the lands therein, located in Marawi City;

Salikata Park, located in the Municipality of Lumba Bayabao; and

Pantuwaraya Lake, located in Saguiaran.

SEC. 2. This Act shall take effect upon its approval.

Approved, May 4, 1965.
